org.freezedry.persistence.keyvalue.renderers

Class FlatteningCollectionRenderer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.freezedry.persistence.keyvalue.renderers.AbstractPersistenceRenderer
      • org.freezedry.persistence.keyvalue.renderers.CollectionRenderer
        • org.freezedry.persistence.keyvalue.renderers.FlatteningCollectionRenderer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Copyable<PersistenceRenderer>, PersistenceRenderer

    public class FlatteningCollectionRenderer
extends CollectionRenderer
    PersistenceRenderer that is used to renderer simple collections that can be flattened, and forwards those that can't be flattened to the CollectionRenderer, it's parent class. The flattening renderer takes a Collection, such as a Set, List, etc, whose elements are either Strings or Numbers, and expresses them as:

    collection = [element1, element2, element3, ..., elementN]

    as opposed to: 

     collection[0] = element1
 collection[1] = element2
 collection[2] = element3
 .
 .
 .
 collection[N-1] = elementN

    Using this renderer for collections of collections will result in the following format: 

     collection[0] = [element11, element12, element13, ..., element1M_1]
 collection[1] = [element21, element22, element23, ..., element2M_2]
 collection[2] = [element31, element32, element33, ..., element3M_3]
 .
 .
 .
 collection[N-1] = [elementN1, elementN2, elementN3, ..., elementNM_N]

    as opposed to: 

     collection[0][0] = element11
 collection[0][1] = element12
 collection[0][2] = element13
 .
 .
 .
 collection[0][M_1-1] = element1M_1
 collection[1][0] = element21
 collection[1][1] = element22
 collection[1][2] = element23
 .
 .
 .
 collection[1][M_2-1] = element2M_2
 collection[2][0] = element31
 collection[2][1] = element32
 collection[2][2] = element33
 .
 .
 .
 collection[2][M_3-1] = element3M_3
 .
 .
 .
 collection[N-1][0] = elementN1
 collection[N-1][1] = elementN2
 collection[N-1][2] = elementN3
 .
 .
 .
 collection[N-1][M_3-1] = elementNM_N

Uses the default the index decorator which prepends a "[" onto the index and appends a "]" to the end of the index. For example, if the index=1 then the index would be decorated to look like [1].

        buildKeyValuePair in interface PersistenceRenderer
        Overrides:
        buildKeyValuePair in class CollectionRenderer
        Parameters:
        infoNode - The current InfoNode in the semantic model.
        key - The current key. The key is constructed by appending persistence names, which may or may not be decorated, to the current key. In this way it represents a flattening of the semantic model.
        keyValues - The current list of key-value pairs
        isWithholdPersistName - true if the renderer implementation should not append the InfoNode's persistence name to the key.
